'''Ismaël Seifallah Gharbi''' ({{langx|aeb|إسماعيل سيفالله غربي}}; born 10 April 2004) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for {{German football updater|Augsburg}} club [[FC Augsburg]], on loan from [[Primeira Liga]] club [[S.C. Braga|Braga]].<ref>{{Soccerway|697397}}</ref> Born in France and a former youth international for France and Spain, he plays for the [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia national team]].

==Club career==
Gharbi began his career at [[Paris FC]] in 2010, and joined the [[Paris Saint-Germain Academy]] in 2016.<ref name=":1" /> In 2020, he was part of the PSG team that participated at the [[Alkass International Cup]] in Qatar, finishing in third place.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|date=24 February 2020|title=[Al Kass International Cup-U16] Mohammed VI Academy (Mar) – PSG 3-3 (2-4 tab)|url=https://www.lestitisdupsg.fr/a-la-une/al-kass-international-cup-u16-mohammed-vi-academy-mar-psg-3-3-2-4-tab/|access-date=30 July 2021|website=Les Titis du PSG|language=fr}}</ref> He scored 5 goals across the tournament; a [[Brace (association football)|brace]] against [[Kashiwa Reysol]] in the group stage,<ref>{{Cite web|date=14 February 2020|title=Gharbi at the double for Perfect Parisians|url=http://internationalcup.alkass.net/u17/newsdetails.php?id=196|access-date=30 July 2021|publisher=[[Al Kass International Cup]]}}</ref> a goal against [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]] in the quarter-finals,<ref>{{Cite web|date=20 February 2020|title=U16 reach the last four!|url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/club/content/paris-saint-germain-fc-zenit-alkass-international-cup-u16-match-report|access-date=30 July 2021|publisher=[[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.]]}}</ref> one against [[Inter Milan Youth Sector|Inter Milan]] in the semi-finals,<ref>{{Cite web|date=23 February 2020|title=[Al Kass International Cup-U16] Inter Milan (Ita) – PSG 3-1 (1-1)|url=https://www.lestitisdupsg.fr/a-la-une/al-kass-international-cup-u16-inter-milan-ita-psg-3-1-1-1/|access-date=30 July 2021|website=Les Titis du PSG|language=fr}}</ref> and another against the [[Mohammed VI Football Academy|Mohammed VI Academy]] in the third place match.<ref name=":0" />

In April 2021, Gharbi was included in the [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] (PSG) squad for the [[UEFA Champions League]] quarter-final first leg against [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]], an eventual 3–2 victory for ''Les Parisiens'' at the [[Allianz Arena]].<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|last=Ben Malek|first=Fakhreddine|date=6 April 2021|title=PSG : Le Tunisien Ismaël Gharbi dans le groupe contre le Bayern Munich|trans-title=PSG: The Tunisian Ismaël Gharbi in the group against Bayern Munich|url=https://sport.tunisienumerique.com/psg-le-tunisien-ismael-gharbi-dans-le-groupe-contre-le-bayern-munich/|access-date=30 July 2021|website=Tunisie Numérique|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Clancy|first=Conor|date=7 April 2021|title=Mbappe shines again as PSG record big win away at Bayern Munich|url=https://bayernstrikes.com/2021/04/07/bayern-munich-narrow-defeat-psg-allianz-arena/|access-date=30 July 2021|website=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]}}</ref> On 14 July 2021, he scored a goal in his first appearance for PSG's senior team, a 4–0 [[Friendly (association football)|friendly]] victory over [[Le Mans FC|Le Mans]] at the [[Camp des Loges]].<ref name=":2">{{Cite web |last=Barbaud |first=Maxime |date=17 July 2021 |title=PSG : Ismaël Gharbi tape à la porte de l'équipe première |trans-title=PSG: Ismaël Gharbi knocks on the door of the first team |url=https://www.footmercato.net/a8586761244508763103-psg-ismael-gharbi-tape-a-la-porte-de-lequipe-premiere |access-date=30 July 2021 |website={{Interlanguage link|Foot Mercato|lt=Foot Mercato|fr|Foot Mercato}} |language=fr}}</ref> On 1 August 2021, Gharbi made his professional debut, coming on as a substitute in a 1–0 [[Trophée des Champions]] loss to [[Lille OSC|Lille]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Lille vs. Paris Saint-Germain|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/lineups?gameId=602883|access-date=31 August 2021|website=[[ESPN]]}}</ref> His [[Coupe de France]] debut came on 19 December in a 3–0 win over [[Entente Feignies Aulnoye FC|Feignies Aulnoye]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Feignies vs. Paris Saint-Germain|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/622436|access-date=19 December 2021|website=[[ESPN]]}}</ref> On 8 May 2022, Gharbi made his first-ever [[Ligue 1]] appearance, coming on as a substitute in a 2–2 draw with [[ES Troyes AC|Troyes]] at the [[Parc des Princes]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=12 May 2022 |title=Ismaël Gharbi: 'It really is a dream' |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/ismaeel-gharbi-it-really-is-a-dream-reactions-paris-saint-germain-troyes-psg-ligue-1 |access-date=8 May 2022 |publisher=[[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.]]}}</ref> He signed his first professional contract with Paris Saint-Germain on 17 June, a three-year deal until 30 June 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |date=17 June 2022 |title=Ismaël Gharbi signs his first professional contract with Paris Saint-Germain |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/ismaeel-gharbi-signs-his-first-professional-contract-with-paris-saint-germain |access-date=17 June 2022 |publisher=[[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.]]}}</ref> In the [[2022–23 Paris Saint-Germain F.C. season|2022–23 season]], he made six league appearances and won his second league title.<ref name=":4">{{Cite web |date=1 September 2023 |title=Ismaël Gharbi joins FC Stade Lausanne Ouchy on loan |url=https://en.psg.fr/teams/first-team/content/ismael-gharbi-paris-saint-germain-joins-fc-stade-lausanne-ouchy-on-loan |access-date=1 September 2023 |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain F.C.}}</ref>

On 1 September 2023, Gharbi was loaned out to [[Swiss Super League]] club [[FC Stade Lausanne Ouchy|Stade Lausanne Ouchy]] until the end of the season.<ref name=":4" /> On 31 August 2024, Gharbi signed for [[Primeira Liga]] club [[S.C. Braga|Braga]] on a five-year contract. Braga paid no transfer fee, but PSG retained 50% of the player's economic rights. A €35 million release clause was included in Gharbi's contract.<ref>{{Cite web |date=31 August 2024 |title=Ismaël Gharbi é Gverreiro! |url=https://scbraga.pt/ismael-gharbi-e-gverreiro/ |access-date=31 August 2024 |publisher=[[S.C. Braga]] |language=pt}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=31 August 2024 |title=Officiel : Le PSG annonce un nouveau départ… à 0€ ! |url=https://le10sport.com/football/mercato/officiel-le-psg-annonce-un-nouveau-depart-a-0eur-711289 |access-date=31 August 2024 |website=Le10Sport |language=fr}}</ref> On 1 September 2025, Gharbi joined [[Bundesliga]] club [[FC Augsburg]] on a season-long loan with an option to buy.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-09-05 |title=Ismaël Gharbi joins FCA on loan |url=https://www.fcaugsburg.de/en/article/ismael-gharbi-joins-fca-on-loan-22351 |access-date=2025-09-05 |website=FC Augsburg |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
Gharbi was born in France to a Tunisian father and Spanish mother,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://okdiario.com/deportes/espana-francia-entran-conflicto-jugador-del-psg-ismael-gharbi-8609922|title=Ismael Gharbi: España y Francia entran en conflicto por el jugador del PSG Ismael Gharb|date=21 February 2022|website=okdiario.com}}</ref> and was therefore eligible to represent France, Spain, and Tunisia.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Jerbi|first=Rania|date=19 July 2021|title=PSG : Le franco-tunisien Ismaël Gharbi se réjouit de sa titularisation|trans-title=PSG: The French-Tunisian Ismaël Gharbi is delighted to have started the match|url=https://africafootunited.com/psg-le-franco-tunisien-ismael-gharbi-se-rejouit-de-sa-titularisation/|access-date=30 July 2021|website=Africa Foot United|language=fr|archive-date=30 July 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210730145638/https://africafootunited.com/psg-le-franco-tunisien-ismael-gharbi-se-rejouit-de-sa-titularisation/|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=":3">{{Cite web|date=17 February 2022|title=PSG: déjà appelé avec la France, Gharbi a reçu une convocation des U18 de l'Espagne|trans-title=PSG: already called up with France, Gharbi has received a call-up with the U18s of Spain|url=https://rmcsport.bfmtv.com/football/equipe-de-france/psg-deja-appele-avec-la-france-gharbi-a-recu-une-convocation-des-u18-de-l-espagne_AV-202202170212.html|access-date=20 February 2022|website=[[RMC Sport]]|language=Fr}}</ref> In 2021, he was called up to play for the [[France national under-18 football team|France under-18s]] for the [[Lafarge Foot Avenir|Tournoi International de Limoges]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=1 September 2021|title=Ismael Gharbi buteur avec la France U18|trans-title=Ismael Gharbi scores with France U18|url=https://www.psg.fr/equipes/equipe-premiere/content/ismael-gharbi-buteur-avec-la-france-u18-france-u18-selections-paris-saint-germain|access-date=1 September 2021|publisher=[[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.]]|language=fr}}</ref> In February 2022, Gharbi was called up to the [[Spain national under-18 football team|Spain under-18s]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=15 February 2022|title=OFICIAL {{!}} Pablo Amo da a conocer la convocatoria para el amistoso ante Dinamarca|trans-title=OFFICIAL {{!}} Pablo Amo announces the call for the friendly against Denmark|url=https://www.sefutbol.com/oficial-pablo-amo-da-conocer-convocatoria-amistoso-dinamarca|access-date=20 February 2022|website=Sefutbol.com|publisher=[[Spain national football team]]|language=es|archive-date=16 August 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220816221845/https://www.sefutbol.com/oficial-pablo-amo-da-conocer-convocatoria-amistoso-dinamarca|url-status=dead}}</ref> In June, he represented Spain at the [[Football at the 2022 Mediterranean Games|2022 Mediterranean Games]] in [[Oran]], Algeria.<ref>{{Cite web |date=28 June 2022 |title=L'Espagne et la France U18 de Gharbi et El Hannach partagent les points |trans-title=Spain and France U18 of Gharbi and El Hannach share the points |url=https://www.psg.fr/equipes/equipe-premiere/content/match-nul-entre-lespagne-de-ismaeel-gharbi-et-la-france-de-younes-el-hannach-u18-paris-saint-germain-2021-2022 |access-date=29 June 2022 |publisher=[[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.]] |language=fr}}</ref>

On 19 August 2025, Gharbi's request to switch international allegiance to Tunisia was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref name="FIFA-Change">{{Cite web|url=https://knowledge.fifa.com/change-of-association-platform|title=FIFA Change of Association Platform|website=knowledge.fifa.com|accessdate=19 August 2025}}<!--sort players by Decision Date. Decision Date: 2025/08/19--></ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=read |first=Foot Africa·1 min |date=2025-08-12 |title=Ismaël Gharbi: Moving toward a first call-up with the Eagles of Carthage? |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/article/isma-l-gharbi-moving-toward-194500154.html |access-date=2025-09-07 |website=Yahoo Sports |language=en-US}}</ref> He earned his first cap on 4 September during a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – CAF Group H|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]] game coming on as a second-half substitute against [[Liberia national football team|Liberia]] at the [[Hammadi Agrebi Stadium]] in [[Tunis]], replacing [[Amor Layouni]] in the 53rd minute; the match ended in a 3–0 victory. On 10 October, he scored his first goal in his third appearance in a 6–0 win over [[São Tomé and Príncipe national football team|São Tomé and Príncipe]] on Day 9 of the 2026 World Cup qualification.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-10-04 |title=Dahmen in squad for Germany win as Saad and Gharbi both score |url=https://www.fcaugsburg.de/en/article/dahmen-in-squad-for-germany-win-as-saad-and-gharbi-both-score-22468 |access-date=2025-10-13 |website=FC Augsburg |language=en}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Gharbi is a versatile player; although primarily an [[attacking midfielder]], he can also play as a [[Wide midfielder|wide]] and [[central midfielder]].<ref name=":2" /> [[Hervé Guégan]], who coached Gharbi at the Alkass International Cup in 2020, has stated that he is a player "technically at ease" and that he "always makes passes with good timing".<ref name=":1" /> Gharbi is good at [[Free kick (association football)|free kicks]] and possesses good ball control. While being able to score himself, he has an ability to make others score.<ref>{{Cite web|date=18 July 2021|title=Gharbi évoque son profil et souligne être fier de jouer avec les professionnels|trans-title=Gharbi talks about his profile and emphasizes being proud to play with the professionals|url=https://www.parisfans.fr/club/gharbi-evoque-son-profil-et-souligne-etre-fier-de-jouer-avec-les-professionnels-551050.html|access-date=10 January 2022|website=ParisFans|language=fr}}</ref> In February 2022, former PSG player [[Mathieu Bodmer]] commented that "in the penalty area, time stops for [Gharbi]" and that he has "cold blood", being able to complete movements at the right moments.<ref name=":3" />

